data.chText: 他在终止冲突的过程中起了重要作用。
data.enText: He was instrumental in bringing about an end to the conflict.

data.chText: 用乐器演奏的；为乐器谱写的
data.enText: made by or for musical instruments
a piece of music (usually popular music) in which only musical instruments are used with no singing
the form of a noun, pronoun or adjective when it refers to a thing that is used to do sth

tr: serving or acting as a means or aid
relating to or designed for or performed on musical instruments

value.def: Someone or something that is instrumental in a process or event helps to make it happen.

example.ex: In his first years as chairman he was instrumental in raising the company's wider profile...
example.tran: 他任董事长的最初几年为提升公司的知名度起到了积极的推动作用。

example.ex: Jesse Jackson was instrumental in the release of some of the hostages.
example.tran: 其中一些人质得以获释多亏了杰西·杰克逊。

value.tran: 有助益的;有帮助的;起作用的

value.def: Instrumental music is performed by instruments and not by voices.

example.ex: ...a cassette recording of vocal and instrumental music.
example.tran: 有声乐也有器乐的磁带录音

example.ex: The last track on the CD is an instrumental.
example.tran: CD 上的最后一支曲目是一首器乐曲。

value.tran: 用乐器演奏(而非声乐)的;为器乐谱写的

trans: 工具变量；辅助变量；工具变量法；辅助变量法；变量法
